\vspace*{10.0cm}  
\baselineskip=18pt  
  
\begin{abstract}  
{\normalsize By combining two distinct
renormalization group transformations, 
opposing  scale transformations, we obtain a composite transformation
which does not rescale the system, and drives it to a
``geometrical" fixed point, controlling the effective geometry
and locality.
The latticized (deconstructed) action for an
extra-dimensional field theory becomes  
a ``perfect action,'' with a linear ladder spectrum 
for $N$ modes. 
} 
\end{abstract}  
  
\vfill  
\end{titlepage}  
  
\baselineskip=18pt  
\renewcommand{\arraystretch}{1.5}
\pagestyle{plain}  
\setcounter{page}{1}
